<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Head</emphasis>
surface smooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7A</figureCitation>
). Labrum with 4 or 5 teeth anteromedially. Ocellaria blackish, with 12-15 (♂) or 17-23 (♀) ommatidia arranged in 1-3 irregular linear rows (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7A</figureCitation>
). Antennae relatively long, reaching back to ring 3; in length, antennomeres 5&gt; 3&gt; 2&gt; 4&gt; 6&gt; 1&gt; 7. Antennomeres 5-7 each with a distodorsal field or corolla of bacilliform sensilla (sensory bacilli). Antennomere 7 with four sensory cones (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7A</figureCitation>
). Gnathochilarium with a separate promentum, lamellae linguales and promentum densely setose, a few setae on mentum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7B</figureCitation>
). Mandible with a large external tooth and an internal tooth, the latter provided with nine cusps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Collum</emphasis>
: crests complete and evident; carinotaxy formula I-III+P+M (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7A</figureCitation>
). Following metaterga strongly crested; carinotaxy formula 2/2+I/i+3/3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A rings 2 - 4, dorsal view B, E mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively C posterior body rings, dorsal view D rings 2 - 5, sublateral view F cross-section of a mid-body ring, caudal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: pf: pleural flap." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705256" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">6</figureCitation>
). Ozoporiferous tubercles very large, much higher than wide. Tegument delicately alveolate-areolate, fine longitudinal striations in front of stricture. Metatergal setae absent. Rings 2 and 3 with long pleural flaps (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A rings 2 - 4, dorsal view B, E mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively C posterior body rings, dorsal view D rings 2 - 5, sublateral view F cross-section of a mid-body ring, caudal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: pf: pleural flap." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705256" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">6D</figureCitation>
). Limbus more or less regularly denticulate.
</paragraph>
