<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Epiproct</emphasis>
simple, very narrow, caudal edge uneven, with a strong central tubercle dorsally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A rings 2 - 4, dorsal view B, E mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively C posterior body rings, dorsal view D rings 2 - 5, sublateral view F cross-section of a mid-body ring, caudal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Abbreviation: pf: pleural flap." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705256" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">6C</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts rather regularly convex, each with several irregular rows of setae. Hypoproct transversely bean-shaped, with 3+3 small setae near caudal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Legs</emphasis>
slender, about 1.2 times as long as mid-body height; claw with a small accessory spine at base, about 1/3 as long as claw (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7F</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 1 very strongly reduced, represented by a sternum showing a pair of small, fused, paramedian, subunciform prongs directed forward, with about 10-11+10-11 long setae at base; flanked by strongly separated, rudimentary, 2-segmented leg vestiges, first segment being much larger (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7D</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 2 slightly hypertrophied, coxae large; penes small, much shorter than coxae, oblong-subtrapeziform, each with two strong setae distolaterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7C</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 3 modified through coxae being especially slender and elongate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7E</figureCitation>
). ♂ femora 6 and 7 normal, without modifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Anterior gonopods</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7H</figureCitation>
) with a broad and plate-shaped coxosternum supporting about 18-20 microsetae near distal margin; apicomesal process of coxite very high, digitiform, tip narrow and hook-shaped. Telopodite large and coiled, 1-segmented, lateral in position, slightly higher than lateral corner of coxite and with a field of 5-10 microspinules at base and 6-8 strong setae apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Posterior gonopods</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7I</figureCitation>
) compact. Coxite subquadrate, with a circular field of 12-15 basolateral microspinules in frontal view and an elongated field of 20-25 microspinules in caudal view; apical and mesal parts of coxite with dense, strong and curved setae. Lamelliform lobe membranous, with a short, distally pectinate flagellum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Vulvae</emphasis>
very simple, bare, modestly emarginate medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Glyphiulus sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A head, collum and antenna B gnathochilarium C penes D leg 1, frontal view E leg 3, frontal view F mid-leg G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I posterior gonopod, caudal view J flagellum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm, (C-I), 0.1 mm (J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705257" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">7G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
In the absence of direct troglomorphic traits, this species can only be considered as troglophilic at most. In the Guangdong Province and in Hong Kong, only 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. formosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="formosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">G. formosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. granulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="granulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">G. granulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recorded as yet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
